CREATE TABLE file_versions (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    file_name VARCHAR(255),
    version_number INT,
    editor VARCHAR(100),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE file_revisions (
    revision_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    file_id INT,
    revision_number INT,
    editor VARCHAR(100),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    changes TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE file_versions (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    file_id UUID,
    version_number INT,
    editor_id UUID,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    content TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE files (
    file_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    file_name VARCHAR,
    file_type VARCHAR,
    owner_id UUID,
    created_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE revisions (
    revision_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    file_id UUID,
    editor_id UUID,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    notes TEXT
);
CREATE TABLE File (file_id INT PRIMARY KEY, file_name VARCHAR(255), file_content TEXT, created_by VARCHAR(100), created_at TIMESTAMP);

CREATE TABLE Version (version_id INT PRIMARY KEY, file_id INT, version_number INT, revision_notes TEXT, modified_by VARCHAR(100), modified_at TIMESTAMP, FOREIGN KEY (file_id) REFERENCES File(file_id) ON DELETE CASCADE);
CREATE TABLE User (user_id INT PRIMARY KEY, username VARCHAR(100), email VARCHAR(255), join_date DATE);

CREATE TABLE Collaboration (collaboration_id INT PRIMARY KEY, file_id INT, user_id INT, collaboration_role VARCHAR(50), join_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (file_id) REFERENCES File(file_id) ON DELETE CASCADE, FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES User(user_id) ON DELETE CASCADE);

CREATE TABLE Comment (comment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, file_id INT, user_id INT, comment_text TEXT, comment_date TIMESTAMP, FOREIGN KEY (file_id) REFERENCES File(file_id) ON DELETE CASCADE, FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES User(user_id) ON DELETE CASCADE);
